# Closing Statement

This framework was built from a single observation (two window screens, one morning) and a series of logical steps. It makes specific predictions. Some are already confirmed to remarkable accuracy. Some will require new experiments. Some require theoretical calculations not yet completed.

A framework that cannot be falsified is not physics. The table above is the commitment. The moiré experiment is the first test, and it can be done this year. Everything else follows from the geometry.

*If the moiré experiment fails, stop here. If it succeeds, the rest of this document applies.*

